# Decide the Observation Schema and Brain Placement

## Question

What IS an observation? Shape (frontmatter fields, provenance: sessionId,
machine, repos, commits-via-ledger, time range), granularity (per session?
per work-thread across sessions? per repo per day?), which Brain root/section
they live in (own root? `observations/` in dark-wizard?), wikilink behavior
(auto-link touched pages?), and the noise bar — what does NOT deserve an
observation. The Mastra extractor idea (structured values: current task,
open questions) adapted to versioned pi schemas like the Bugle's.

## Resolution (2026-07-12, grilled with Joel — approved)

**Unit**: per-session observation atoms; the reflector composes cross-session
thread pages later (Observer→Reflector split). **Placement**:
`dark-wizard/.brain/observations/YYYY-MM-DD-<machine>-<agent>-<slug>.svx` →
renders at `/user/observations/…`, auto-wikilinked to touched project/resource
pages (graph nodes for free).

**Schema v1 frontmatter**: `type: observation`, `schemaVersion: 1`,
`sessionId`, `machine`, `agent` (pi|claude|codex), `started`, `ended`,
`tokens`, `repos[]`, `commits[]` (hash-proven where the change ledger runs,
best-effort elsewhere — coverage research receipt), `derivation {kind:
pi-agent, model, promptHash}`. Body: one-paragraph gist; `## Observations`
(dense, transcript-grounded bullets); `## Decisions` (wikilinked); `## Open
questions / next actions`. Extractors are body sections behind a versioned
pi prompt (Bugle pattern), not separate machinery.

**Noise bar**: no ledger-proven mutations AND under ~15k tokens → no page,
one line in that day's observation index (skipped ≠ invisible).

`derivation.promptHash` is load-bearing: it's what makes distilled memory
auditable months later. Prototype may amend all of this — that's its job.

## Amendment (Joel, 2026-07-12): epoch atoms

The atom is a SESSION EPOCH, not a whole session: an observation page covers
the new-activity window since the last observation of that session
(frontmatter gains window bounds; multiple pages per sessionId over its
life). The reflector composes per-session and per-thread views from epochs.
